devdoc.details: Contract module which provides a basic access control mechanism, where there is an account (an owner) that can be granted exclusive access to specific functions. The initial owner is set to the address provided by the deployer. This can later be changed with {transferOwnership}. This module is used through inheritance. It will make available the modifier `onlyOwner`, which can be applied to your functions to restrict their use to the owner.

OwnableInvalidOwner(address).details: The owner is not a valid owner account. (eg. `address(0)`)

OwnableUnauthorizedAccount(address).details: The caller account is not authorized to perform an operation.

constructor.details: Initializes the contract setting the address provided by the deployer as the initial owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

Approval(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `owner` enables `approved` to manage the `tokenId` token.

ApprovalForAll(address,address,bool).details: Emitted when `owner` enables or disables (`approved`) `operator` to manage all of its assets.

BatchMetadataUpdate(uint256,uint256).details: This event emits when the metadata of a range of tokens is changed. So that the third-party platforms such as NFT market could timely update the images and related attributes of the NFTs.

MetadataUpdate(uint256).details: This event emits when the metadata of a token is changed. So that the third-party platforms such as NFT market could timely update the images and related attributes of the NFT.

Transfer(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `tokenId` token is transferred from `from` to `to`.

approve(address,uint256).details: Gives permission to `to` to transfer `tokenId` token to another account. The approval is cleared when the token is transferred. Only a single account can be approved at a time, so approving the zero address clears previous approvals. Requirements: - The caller must own the token or be an approved operator. - `tokenId` must exist. Emits an {Approval} event.

balanceOf(address).details: Returns the number of tokens in ``owner``'s account.

getApproved(uint256).details: Returns the account approved for `tokenId` token. Requirements: - `tokenId` must exist.

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Returns if the `operator` is allowed to manage all of the assets of `owner`. See {setApprovalForAll}

ownerOf(uint256).details: Returns the owner of the `tokenId` token. Requirements: - `tokenId` must exist.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Safely transfers `tokenId` token from `from` to `to`, checking first that contract recipients are aware of the ERC721 protocol to prevent tokens from being forever locked. Requirements: - `from` cannot be the zero address. - `to` cannot be the zero address. - `tokenId` token must exist and be owned by `from`. - If the caller is not `from`, it must have been allowed to move this token by either {approve} or   {setApprovalForAll}. - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC721Receiver-onERC721Received}, which is called upon   a safe transfer. safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Safely transfers `tokenId` token from `from` to `to`, checking first that contract recipients are aware of the ERC721 protocol to prevent tokens from being forever locked. Requirements: - `from` cannot be the zero address. - `to` cannot be the zero address. - `tokenId` token must exist and be owned by `from`. - If the caller is not `from`, it must have been allowed to move this token by either {approve} or   {setApprovalForAll}. - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC721Receiver-onERC721Received}, which is called upon   a safe transfer. Emits a {Transfer} event.

devdoc.details: Provides information about the current execution context, including the sender of the transaction and its data. While these are generally available via msg.sender and msg.data, they should not be accessed in such a direct manner, since when dealing with meta-transactions the account sending and paying for execution may not be the actual sender (as far as an application is concerned). This contract is only required for intermediate, library-like contracts.

Contract module that helps prevent reentrant calls to a function. Inheriting from `ReentrancyGuard` will make the {nonReentrant} modifier available, which can be applied to functions to make sure there are no nested (reentrant) calls to them. Note that because there is a single `nonReentrant` guard, functions marked as `nonReentrant` may not call one another. This can be worked around by making those functions `private`, and then adding `external` `nonReentrant` entry points to them. TIP: If you would like to learn more about reentrancy and alternative ways to protect against it, check out our blog post https://blog.openzeppelin.com/reentrancy-after-istanbul/[Reentrancy After Istanbul].

devdoc.details: Implementation of the {IERC165} interface. Contracts that want to implement ERC165 should inherit from this contract and override {supportsInterface} to check for the additional interface id that will be supported. For example: ```solidity function supportsInterface(bytes4 interfaceId) public view virtual override returns (bool) {     return interfaceId == type(MyInterface).interfaceId || super.supportsInterface(interfaceId); } ```

Interface of the ERC165 standard, as defined in the https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165[EIP]. Implementers can declare support of contract interfaces, which can then be queried by others ({ERC165Checker}). For an implementation, see {ERC165}.

}\n}\n","keccak256":"0x5f7e4076e175393767754387c962926577f1660dd9b810187b9002407656be72","license":"MIT"},"contracts/NFT.sol":{"content":"// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.20;\r\n\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC721/extensions/ERC721URIStorage.sol\";\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC721/extensions/ERC721Enumerable.sol\";\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/access/Ownable.sol\";\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/utils/ReentrancyGuard.sol\";\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/utils/Strings.sol\";\r\n\r\n/**\r\n * @title WalletConnectNFT\r\n * @dev Complete NFT contract with minting, metadata, and WalletConnect optimization\r\n * @notice This contract is designed for easy integration with WalletConnect\r\n */\r\ncontract WalletConnectNFT is ERC721URIStorage, ERC721Enumerable, Ownable, ReentrancyGuard {\r\n    using Strings for uint256;\r\n\r\n    // ============ State Variables ============\r\n    \r\n    uint256 private _tokenIds;\r\n    \r\n    // Collection info\r\n    string public baseTokenURI;\r\n    string public collectionDescription = \"WalletConnect NFT Collection - Mint your unique digital asset!\";\r\n    \r\n    // Minting configuration\r\n    uint256 public mintPrice = 0.001 ether; // Affordable for testing\r\n    uint256 public maxSupply = 10000;\r\n    uint256 public maxMintPerWallet = 10;\r\n    bool public mintingEnabled = true;\r\n    bool public publicMintEnabled = true;\r\n    \r\n    // Whitelist for presale\r\n    mapping(address => bool) public whitelist;\r\n    mapping(address => uint256) public mintedPerWallet;\r\n    \r\n    // Royalties (EIP-2981)\r\n    address public royaltyReceiver;\r\n    uint96 public royaltyFeeNumerator = 500; // 5% = 500/10000\r\n\r\n    // ============ Events ============\r\n    \r\n    event NFTMinted(\r\n        address indexed minter,\r\n        uint256 indexed tokenId,\r\n        string tokenURI,\r\n        uint256 mintPrice\r\n    );\r\n    event MintPriceUpdated(uint256 oldPrice, uint256 newPrice);\r\n    event MintingToggled(bool enabled);\r\n    event PublicMintToggled(bool enabled);\r\n    event BaseURIUpdated(string newBaseURI);\r\n    event WhitelistUpdated(address indexed user, bool status);\r\n    event Withdrawn(address indexed owner, uint256 amount);\r\n\r\n    // ============ Constructor ============\r\n\r\n    constructor(\r\n        string memory _name,\r\n        string memory _symbol,\r\n        string memory _baseTokenURI\r\n    ) ERC721(_name, _symbol) Ownable(msg.sender) {\r\n        baseTokenURI = _baseTokenURI;\r\n        royaltyReceiver = msg.sender;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // ============ Minting Functions ============\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Public mint function - main entry point for users\r\n     * @param _tokenURI IPFS URI for the NFT metadata\r\n     */\r\n    function mint(string memory _tokenURI) external payable nonReentrant returns (uint256) {\r\n        require(mintingEnabled, \"Minting is disabled\");\r\n        require(publicMintEnabled || whitelist[msg.sender], \"Public mint not enabled\");\r\n        require(_tokenIds < maxSupply, \"Max supply reached\");\r\n        require(msg.value >= mintPrice, \"Insufficient payment\");\r\n        require(\r\n            mintedPerWallet[msg.sender] < maxMintPerWallet,\r\n            \"Exceeded max mint per wallet\"\r\n        );\r\n        require(bytes(_tokenURI).length > 0, \"Token URI cannot be empty\");\r\n\r\n        return _mintNFT(msg.sender, _tokenURI);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Batch mint multiple NFTs in one transaction\r\n     * @param _tokenURIs Array of IPFS URIs\r\n     */\r\n    function mintBatch(string[] memory _tokenURIs) \r\n        external \r\n        payable \r\n        nonReentrant \r\n        returns (uint256[] memory) \r\n    {\r\n        require(mintingEnabled, \"Minting is disabled\");\r\n        require(publicMintEnabled || whitelist[msg.sender], \"Public mint not enabled\");\r\n        require(_tokenURIs.length > 0, \"Must mint at least 1\");\r\n        require(_tokenURIs.length <= 20, \"Maximum 20 per transaction\");\r\n        require(\r\n            _tokenIds + _tokenURIs.length <= maxSupply,\r\n            \"Would exceed max supply\"\r\n        );\r\n        require(\r\n            msg.value >= mintPrice * _tokenURIs.length,\r\n            \"Insufficient payment\"\r\n        );\r\n        require(\r\n            mintedPerWallet[msg.sender] + _tokenURIs.length <= maxMintPerWallet,\r\n            \"Would exceed max mint per wallet\"\r\n        );\r\n\r\n        uint256[] memory tokenIds = new uint256[](_tokenURIs.length);\r\n\r\n        for (uint256 i = 0; i < _tokenURIs.length; i++) {\r\n            tokenIds[i] = _mintNFT(msg.sender, _tokenURIs[i]);\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        return tokenIds;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Free mint for whitelisted addresses\r\n     * @param _tokenURI IPFS URI for the NFT metadata\r\n     */\r\n    function freeMint(string memory _tokenURI) external nonReentrant returns (uint256) {\r\n        require(mintingEnabled, \"Minting is disabled\");\r\n        require(whitelist[msg.sender], \"Not whitelisted\");\r\n        require(_tokenIds < maxSupply, \"Max supply reached\");\r\n        require(\r\n            mintedPerWallet[msg.sender] < maxMintPerWallet,\r\n            \"Exceeded max mint per wallet\"\r\n        );\r\n\r\n        return _mintNFT(msg.sender, _tokenURI);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Owner can mint to any address (for giveaways, etc.)\r\n     * @param _to Recipient address\r\n     * @param _tokenURI IPFS URI for the NFT metadata\r\n     */\r\n    function mintTo(address _to, string memory _tokenURI) \r\n        external \r\n        onlyOwner \r\n        returns (uint256) \r\n    {\r\n        require(_tokenIds < maxSupply, \"Max supply reached\");\r\n        return _mintNFT(_to, _tokenURI);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Internal minting logic\r\n     */\r\n    function _mintNFT(address _to, string memory _tokenURI) \r\n        private \r\n        returns (uint256) \r\n    {\r\n        _tokenIds++;\r\n        uint256 newTokenId = _tokenIds;\r\n\r\n        _safeMint(_to, newTokenId);\r\n        _setTokenURI(newTokenId, _tokenURI);\r\n\r\n        mintedPerWallet[_to]++;\r\n\r\n        emit NFTMinted(_to, newTokenId, _tokenURI, msg.value);\r\n\r\n        return newTokenId;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // ============ View Functions ============\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get total minted supply\r\n     */\r\n    function totalSupply() public view override(ERC721Enumerable) returns (uint256) {\r\n        return _tokenIds;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get all token IDs owned by an address\r\n     */\r\n    function tokensOfOwner(address _owner) \r\n        external \r\n        view \r\n        returns (uint256[] memory) \r\n    {\r\n        uint256 tokenCount = balanceOf(_owner);\r\n        uint256[] memory tokenIds = new uint256[](tokenCount);\r\n\r\n        for (uint256 i = 0; i < tokenCount; i++) {\r\n            tokenIds[i] = tokenOfOwnerByIndex(_owner, i);\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        return tokenIds;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get detailed token information\r\n     */\r\n    function getTokenInfo(uint256 _tokenId) \r\n        external \r\n        view \r\n        returns (\r\n            address owner,\r\n            string memory uri,\r\n            bool exists\r\n        ) \r\n    {\r\n        exists = _ownerOf(_tokenId) != address(0);\r\n        if (exists) {\r\n            owner = ownerOf(_tokenId);\r\n            uri = tokenURI(_tokenId);\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get minting statistics for an address\r\n     */\r\n    function getMintStats(address _user) \r\n        external \r\n        view \r\n        returns (\r\n            uint256 minted,\r\n            uint256 remaining,\r\n            bool isWhitelisted,\r\n            uint256 price\r\n        ) \r\n    {\r\n        minted = mintedPerWallet[_user];\r\n        remaining = maxMintPerWallet - minted;\r\n        isWhitelisted = whitelist[_user];\r\n        price = mintPrice;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get collection statistics\r\n     */\r\n    function getCollectionStats() \r\n        external \r\n        view \r\n        returns (\r\n            uint256 currentSupply,\r\n            uint256 maxSupply_,\r\n            uint256 mintPrice_,\r\n            bool mintingEnabled_,\r\n            bool publicMintEnabled_\r\n        ) \r\n    {\r\n        return (\r\n            _tokenIds,\r\n            maxSupply,\r\n            mintPrice,\r\n            mintingEnabled,\r\n            publicMintEnabled\r\n        );\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Override for base URI\r\n     */\r\n    function _baseURI() internal view virtual override returns (string memory) {\r\n        return baseTokenURI;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Override tokenURI to support both base URI and custom URIs\r\n     */\r\n    function tokenURI(uint256 _tokenId)\r\n        public\r\n        view\r\n        override(ERC721, ERC721URIStorage)\r\n        returns (string memory)\r\n    {\r\n        return super.tokenURI(_tokenId);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // ============ Whitelist Functions ============\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Add address to whitelist\r\n     */\r\n    function addToWhitelist(address _user) external onlyOwner {\r\n        whitelist[_user] = true;\r\n        emit WhitelistUpdated(_user, true);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Add multiple addresses to whitelist\r\n     */\r\n    function addToWhitelistBatch(address[] calldata _users) external onlyOwner {\r\n        for (uint256 i = 0; i < _users.length; i++) {\r\n            whitelist[_users[i]] = true;\r\n            emit WhitelistUpdated(_users[i], true);\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Remove address from whitelist\r\n     */\r\n    function removeFromWhitelist(address _user) external onlyOwner {\r\n        whitelist[_user] = false;\r\n        emit WhitelistUpdated(_user, false);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // ============ Admin Functions ============\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Update mint price\r\n     */\r\n    function setMintPrice(uint256 _newPrice) external onlyOwner {\r\n        uint256 oldPrice = mintPrice;\r\n        mintPrice = _newPrice;\r\n        emit MintPriceUpdated(oldPrice, _newPrice);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Update max supply\r\n     */\r\n    function setMaxSupply(uint256 _newMaxSupply) external onlyOwner {\r\n        require(_newMaxSupply >= _tokenIds, \"Cannot set below current supply\");\r\n        maxSupply = _newMaxSupply;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Update max mint per wallet\r\n     */\r\n    function setMaxMintPerWallet(uint256 _newMax) external onlyOwner {\r\n        maxMintPerWallet = _newMax;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Toggle minting on/off\r\n     */\r\n    function toggleMinting() external onlyOwner {\r\n        mintingEnabled = !mintingEnabled;\r\n        emit MintingToggled(mintingEnabled);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Toggle public minting on/off\r\n     */\r\n    function togglePublicMint() external onlyOwner {\r\n        publicMintEnabled = !publicMintEnabled;\r\n        emit PublicMintToggled(publicMintEnabled);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Update base URI\r\n     */\r\n    function setBaseURI(string memory _newBaseURI) external onlyOwner {\r\n        baseTokenURI = _newBaseURI;\r\n        emit BaseURIUpdated(_newBaseURI);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Update collection description\r\n     */\r\n    function setCollectionDescription(string memory _description) external onlyOwner {\r\n        collectionDescription = _description;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Update royalty info\r\n     */\r\n    function setRoyaltyInfo(address _receiver, uint96 _feeNumerator) external onlyOwner {\r\n        require(_feeNumerator <= 1000, \"Royalty fee too high\"); // Max 10%\r\n        royaltyReceiver = _receiver;\r\n        royaltyFeeNumerator = _feeNumerator;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // ============ Withdraw Functions ============\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Withdraw contract balance to owner\r\n     */\r\n    function withdraw() external onlyOwner nonReentrant {\r\n        uint256 balance = address(this).balance;\r\n        require(balance > 0, \"No funds to withdraw\");\r\n        \r\n        (bool success, ) = payable(owner()).call{value: balance}(\"\");\r\n        require(success, \"Withdrawal failed\");\r\n        \r\n        emit Withdrawn(owner(), balance);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Withdraw specific amount\r\n     */\r\n    function withdrawAmount(uint256 _amount) external onlyOwner nonReentrant {\r\n        require(_amount <= address(this).balance, \"Insufficient balance\");\r\n        \r\n        (bool success, ) = payable(owner()).call{value: _amount}(\"\");\r\n        require(success, \"Withdrawal failed\");\r\n        \r\n        emit Withdrawn(owner(), _amount);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // ============ Royalty Functions (EIP-2981) ============\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Returns royalty info for a token\r\n     */\r\n    function royaltyInfo(uint256 _tokenId, uint256 _salePrice)\r\n        external\r\n        view\r\n        returns (address receiver, uint256 royaltyAmount)\r\n    {\r\n        receiver = royaltyReceiver;\r\n        royaltyAmount = (_salePrice * royaltyFeeNumerator) / 10000;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // ============ OpenSea Integration ============\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Contract-level metadata for OpenSea\r\n     */\r\n    function contractURI() public view returns (string memory) {\r\n        return string(\r\n            abi.encodePacked(\r\n                baseTokenURI,\r\n                \"collection.json\"\r\n            )\r\n        );\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // ============ Required Overrides ============\r\n\r\n    function _update(address to, uint256 tokenId, address auth)\r\n        internal\r\n        override(ERC721, ERC721Enumerable)\r\n        returns (address)\r\n    {\r\n        return super._update(to, tokenId, auth);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function _increaseBalance(address account, uint128 value)\r\n        internal\r\n        override(ERC721, ERC721Enumerable)\r\n    {\r\n        super._increaseBalance(account, value);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function supportsInterface(bytes4 interfaceId)\r\n        public\r\n        view\r\n        override(ERC721URIStorage, ERC721Enumerable)\r\n        returns (bool)\r\n    {\r\n        return super.supportsInterface(interfaceId);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // ============ Emergency Functions ============\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Pause all minting in case of emergency\r\n     */\r\n    function emergencyPause() external onlyOwner {\r\n        mintingEnabled = false;\r\n        publicMintEnabled = false;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Resume minting after emergency\r\n     */\r\n    function emergencyUnpause() external onlyOwner {\r\n        mintingEnabled = true;\r\n        publicMintEnabled = true;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Receive ETH\r\n     */\r\n    receive() external payable {}\r\n}","keccak256":"0x067c33da2640054b98b78a3c74d681c26af442d3c88275776e6530551567ae9d","license":"MIT"}},"version":1}
